\begin{equation*}
\lr{ \Bv \wedge \Bu } \cdot \Bw = \Bv \lr{ \Bu \cdot \Bw } - \Bu \lr{ \Bv \cdot \Bw }
\end{equation*}
With \( \Bw = 1/\Bu = \Bu/\Bu^2 \), this is
\begin{equation*}
\begin{aligned}
\lr{ \Bv \wedge \Bu } \cdot \inv{\Bu} 
&= \Bv \lr{ \Bu \cdot \inv{\Bu} } - \Bu \lr{ \Bv \cdot \inv{\Bu} } \\
&= \Bv - \lr{ \Bv \cdot \Bu } \inv{\Bu}
\end{aligned}
\end{equation*}


